parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Passenger Seat Occupancy Sensor Mat Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger seat occupancy sensor mat can cause the airbag to malfunction, leading to potential injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is on
the passenger airbag is not detected
the passenger airbag is not deploying
the "Airbag warning lamp" or "Passenger Airbag OFF" lamp is activated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag control unit can cause the airbag to malfunction, leading to potential injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is on
the airbag is not deploying
the airbag control unit is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can cause a delay in fixing safety issues, leaving vehicles on the road with potential safety hazards.
symptoms: The dealer is unable to obtain parts
the manufacturer is unable to provide a timeline for part availability
the recall repair is delayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system and uncontrolled acceleration can cause accidents, leading to potential injury or fatality.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates out of control
the brakes fail
the power steering failure warning is displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive brake pedal travel can cause delayed or inadequate braking, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially in low-speed situations like parking or approaching stop signs.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels an abnormally long distance before the brakes engage
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes do not respond immediately
the brakes require pumping to engage
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power steering can cause the vehicle to become difficult or impossible to steer, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds or in tight spaces.
symptoms: The power steering fails or becomes intermittent
making the vehicle hard to steer
the steering feels manual or heavy
the steering suddenly freezes or becomes stuck
the vehicle veers in an unintended direction while steering
the Power Steering Malfunction warning light appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's transmission fault can cause the vehicle to jerk or lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into jerking mode while driving without warning
the safety light comes on as transmission fault
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Leaks due to Timing Case Bolt Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing case bolts can cause engine oil leaks, which can lead to engine damage and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Engine oil leaking from the timing case over bolts
oil leaking from the valve cover gasket onto the side of the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Control Fault and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine control fault can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the "engine control fault" indicator illuminates
the vehicle stalls.
